<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/28> rdfs:label "Secondary Source: Rüpke 2005" ;
	a dprr:SecondarySource ;
	dprr:hasName "Rüpke" ;
	dprr:hasBiblio "Rüpke, J., Fasti sacerdotum : die Mitglieder der Priesterschaften und das sakrale Funktionspersonal römischer, griechischer, orientalischer und jüdisch-christlicher Kulte in der Stadt Rom von 300 v. Chr. bis 499 n. Chr. / von Jörg Rüpke ; unter Beifügung einer CD zur Erschliessung des prosopographischen Materials von Bernd Nüsslein ; unter Mitarbeit von Helmut Pannke. Wiesbaden : Steiner, 2005." ;
	dprr:hasAbbreviation "Rüpke 2005" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8323> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8323" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Dom. 127." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7236> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7236" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Rex sacrorum. Note Shackleton Bailey's suggestion (Studies 25-26), made because the praenomen Lucius was banned among the patrician Claudii (Suet. Tib. 1.2), that the gentilicium of the rex sacrorum of 57 (Har. Resp. 12; but cf. Dom. 127 a gentili tuo) should possibly be emended to L. Cloulius, perhaps a descendant of P. Cloelius Siculus, who was appointed rex sacrorum in 180. But the rex is addressed as a gentilis of Clodius in Dom. 127. Shackleton Bailey, Onom., has withdrawn his suggestion and accepts L. Claudius.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5115> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5115" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The full list of the college of Pontifices, including the Flamen Martialis and the Flamen Quirinalis (no Flamen Dialis had been inaugurated since the death of Merula in 87) and the Pontifices Minores, as it was composed on September 29, 57, can be reconstructed from Cic. Har. Resp. 12:" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4990> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4990" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Har. Resp. 12; cf. Dom. 127." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4989> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4989" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "4 The order in Cic. Har. Resp. 12 indicates that L. Claudius was inaugurated before 60 B. C. The praenomen has been doubted since it was avoided in the Claudian family (Suet. Tib. 1-2; cf. Gell. 9.2.11), but it appears also in Val. Max. 8.1.6." .
